      "caption_text": "We keep coming back for a reason \ud83d\udc3a\ud83d\udca6\n\nWe\u2019ve been visiting @greatwolflodge Poconos for years, and it\u2019s always a hit. Here\u2019s exactly how we make the most of every trip:\n\n\u2022 Get the Wolf Pass. It\u2019s the easiest way to enjoy so many activities in one go. Our favorites are Ten Paw Alley, Moon Mini Golf, the Moonstone Mirror Maze, Candy Cup, and picking out a Build-A-Bear furry friend.\n\n\u2022 Stay in the suites at Mountain Tower. They\u2019re roomy, modern, and perfect for families. We stayed in the KidCabin Suite and the kids were obsessed with the bunk beds.\n\n\u2022 Book an indoor cabana at the water park. It\u2019s a great home base for the day with seating, storage for your things, and a server so you can order lunch and drinks while the kids keep playing.\n\n\u2022 Plan your meals. We like dinner at Fireside Restaurant (reservations recommended) and breakfast buffet at Timbers Table & Kitchen.\n\nA fun, easy, and memory-filled trip every single time \ud83e\udd0dThank you Great Wolf Lodge for hosting us! #hosted #GreatWolfLodge\n.\n.\n.\n.\n.\nGreat Wolf Lodge, Poconos, Pennsylvania, PA, spring break, family of 5, family of five, family tirps, weekend getaway, family photos, mom life, motherhood through Instagram, parents of Instagram, Philly blogger, Asian blogger, Philadelphia blogger, Philly influencer",
